midfielddata

Sample of the MIDFIELD Student Unit Record Data

The goal of midfielddata is to provide a sample of MIDFIELD data for practice working with longitudinal, de-identified, individual student unit records.

Overview

MIDFIELD (as of June 2022) contains Student Unit Records (SURs) of 1.7M undergraduates at nineteen US institutions from 1987 through 2018, though different institutions provide data over different time spans. MIDFIELD is large enough to permit summarizing by multiple characteristics such as race/ethnicity, sex, and program.

midfieldr is an R package that provides tools for working with MIDFIELD research data and with the practice data in the midfielddata R package.

midfielddata is an R data package that provides practice data (a proportionate stratified sample of MIDFIELD) with longitudinal SURs for nearly 98,000 undergraduates at 12 institutions from 1987–2016 organized in four data tables:

Practice data table Each row is No. of rows No. of columns Memory
student a degree-seeking student 97,640 13 19 Mb
course a student in a course 3.5M 12 340 Mb
term a student in a term 728,000 13 80 Mb
degree a student who graduates 48,000 5 10.2 Mb

Usage 

# Load the package
library("midfielddata")

# Load individual data tables as needed
data(student)
data(term)
data(course)
data(degree)

# Alternatively, load several tables with one line
data(student, term, degree)

Requirements

  • R (>= 3.5.0)

Installation

Because of the size of the data tables, installing midfielddata takes time; please be patient and wait for the prompt “>” to reappear. In the Console, run:

# Type in the Console
install.packages("midfielddata",
  repos = "https://MIDFIELDR.github.io/drat/",
  type = "source"
)
# be patient

You can confirm a successful installation by running the following lines to bring up the package help page in the Help window.

# Confirm successful installation
library("midfielddata")
help("midfielddata-package")

Build
